  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the fish fillets and cook until browned on both sides, about 3 minutes per side.",
    "Remove the fish from the pot and set aside.",
    "Reduce heat to medium and add the garlic, onion, bell pepper, and tomato to the pot.",
    "Cook until the vegetables are softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the scotch bonnet peppers, allspice, thyme, salt, and black pepper to the pot, and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the vanilla pod, coconut milk, and water to the pot, and stir to combine.",
    "Return the fish to the pot and simmer until cooked through, about 8-10 minutes.",
    "Stir in the gluten-free flour to thicken the stew.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with chopped fresh herbs if desired."
  ],
